main event: A woman reported seeing an oval-shaped object, approximately the size of a spinning top, that was yellow-orange in color and stationary in the sky over Sacramento, California on August 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object did not move while it was being viewed.
The woman stated that the pattern of lights on the object was unusual.
An aircraft had departed McClellan Air Force Base shortly before the sighting, but the investigators were not sure if this was related to the reported object.
The woman was described as being unsure of what she had seen.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were clear with good visibility.
sighted object: oval-shaped object, approximately the size of a spinning top, yellow-orange in color
